# Core Rules

## Absolute Prohibitions
- NEVER run `git commit` under any circumstances — not even with `--no-verify`
- NEVER run `git push`, `git push --force`, or any remote write operation
- NEVER delete files without explicit user confirmation
- NEVER drop or truncate database collections/tables
- NEVER modify `.env` files unless explicitly asked
- NEVER install packages without asking first

## Before Starting Any Task
- Read `conductor/product.md` and `conductor/tech-stack.md` to understand the project context
- Check `conductor/decisions.md` to avoid re-debating already resolved decisions
- If the task is ambiguous, ask one clarifying question before proceeding

## When You're Unsure
- Stop and ask — do not assume and proceed
- Prefer doing less and confirming over doing more and breaking things
- If a change affects more than 3 files, summarize the plan and wait for approval

## Session Behavior
- Do not summarize what you just did unless asked
- Do not add code comments explaining what the code does — only explain non-obvious intent
- Keep responses focused — avoid padding with unnecessary explanations
